-- CLSA appoints ex-Macquarie banker to head i-banking
-- By Swati Pandey
-- Mon Dec 08, 2014 06:56PM EST
-- None



SYDNEY, Dec 9 (Reuters) - CLSA, owned by Citic Securities Co Ltd <600030.SS>, has appointed former Macquarie Group <MQG.AX> banker Andrew Low to head its international investment banking arm as the Hong Kong-based brokerage and investment firm looks to expand across Asia.

Low will be based in Hong Kong and report to CLSA Chairman and CEO Jonathan Slone. "In Andrew, we will have at the helm one of Asia's most experienced and respected investment bankers to expand our offering, drive revenue and extend the footprint," Slone said in a statement.